reviewer_text.reviewer_text: I had an ocular in Shang Mactan and this restaurant was said to be one of their bests so I gave it a try. Delicious food, staff were accommodating and generous servings.

What we had:
Sweet and sour soup, yang chow rice, roast chicken, pork knuckles, tiger prawn, chilled glutinous rice with mango filling

What I loved:
Great great Chinese food. For Shangri-La price, ToS I guess is most affordable. Serving is generous, but most of all the service was commendable. Very professional, accommodating, warm staff here. They change your plates as needed, and even offer to help with the prawn. (I have allergies to shrimp but the tiger prawn my friend had sure did look so delicious!) The roast chicken ang yang chow was so good! And the mochi-like dessert with fresh mangoes was a bonus.  ðŸ¥°

title: Giuseppe
address: Paseo Saturnino, Ma. Luisa Road, Banilad, Cebu City

reviewer_text.reviewer_text: Our fam's all-time fave place to dine... Their Osso buco is to die for with a perfectly cooked and flavorful risotto. We also love their four cheese pizza (Quattro Formaggi) and Gregorio. Ambiance is great and the servers are very polite and accommodating. I highly recommend!

Giuseppe has never disappointed me when it comes to how their food tastes. I ate at their branch in Panglao twice before and was met here with the same delicious food I was expecting.

The only downside is that it's a bit pricey, but in this case I can definitely say the food is worth the money. Actually, not just the food. The place has great ambiance and the servers are very friendly and accommodating. The parking is limited though, and a bit elevated up front but you can park in the side street. I suppose a last resort option would be to try parking at Streetscape if it's really busy.

reviewer_text.reviewer_text: great ambience and great coffee
